    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1958-09-25T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1958-09-25T12:00:00-05:00" n="126"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d126">
                <head>126. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in Poland</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d126fn0">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 611.93/9–2558. Secret; <gloss target="#t_Niact1">Niact</gloss>; Limit
                        Distribution. Received at 2:26 p.m. Repeated priority to USUN and <gloss
                            target="#t_Niact1">niact</gloss> to Taipei.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Warsaw</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1958-09-25T19:00:00+02:00">September 25, 1958, 7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>476. USUN for Lodge. <persName corresp="#p_BJD1"
                        >Beam</persName>–<persName>Wang</persName> Talks. Comments today’s meeting: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>
                            <persName>Wang</persName>’s position continues hard and unyielding. He
                            shows no disposition make concessions to US viewpoint which would be
                            required if real negotiation to result.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>
                            <persName>Wang</persName> gave impression of man marking time. His
                            presentation was a strong but routine recapitulation <gloss
                                target="#t_ChiCom1">ChiCom</gloss> position. Not only produced
                            nothing new himself but made no effort probe US intentions. Neither did
                            he accuse US of stalling or otherwise attempt pressure US to come up
                            with new proposals. In response our expression preference for morning
                            meeting time he preferred Tuesday to Monday.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>
                            <persName>Wang</persName>’s reference to US press not supporting
                            government’s position may be significant. Although could be merely
                            convenient debating point might also mean <gloss target="#t_ChiCom1"
                                >ChiCom</gloss>’s are confident opposition to US military
                            intervention both within US and among allies may effectively prevent
                            such intervention.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="strong">
                            <persName corresp="#p_BJD1">Beam</persName>
                        </hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
